     "source": [
      "Part 2: Configuration and Deployment\n",
      "\n",
      "Elastic = Distribution across cluster (scaling, fault tolerance)\n",
      "- Shards\n",
      "- Nodes\n",
      "\n",
      "number_of_shards: 3\n",
      "number_of_replicas: 2\n",
      "\n",
      "Shards:\n",
      "- Chunks of index searched independently (parallelization)\n",
      "- Create an index is when you choose shards\n",
      "- More shards helps lots of data, but overhead means collation\n",
      "- Good for small queries\n",
      "\n",
      "Replicas:\n",
      "- More queries can be spread out on shards\n",
      "\n",
      "Can see a throughput hit with more shards and collation takes a hit too\n",
      "\n",
      "Too many replicas slow down inserts as well as taking up ram and disk space\n",
      "\n",
      "Recommendations: (based on one index)\n",
      "- Have at least one replica\n",
      "- Make sure you have pleny of shards, over provision but don't go crazy, can't fix later\n",
      "- 3 eligible masters\n",
      "-- discovery.zen.minimum_master_nodes: 2\n",
      "\n",
      "Protect with firewall\n",
      "- It's too friendly\n",
      "- Turn off multicast\n",
      "- turn on unicast, list nodes\n",
      "- name cluster name something weird\n",
      "\n",
      "To add new node without downtime:\n",
      "- New hosts in discovery.zen.ping.unicast.hosts: [name, name, new_name]\n",
      "- Configs when you're ready\n",
      "\n",
      "Be wary:\n",
      "- new versions of elasticsearch may break things\n",
      "- behavior changes, bugs\n",
      "- qualify before upgrading\n",
      "\n",
      "Monitoring:\n",
      "- cluster health api\n",
      "- 'http://localhost:9200/_cluster/health?pretty=true'\n",
      "- status color, yellow -> green -> yellow\n",
      "- check number of nodes key, not just status color\n",
      "- check number of shards\n",
      "\n",
      "elasticsearch-paramedic - JS\n",
      "- http://karmi.github.com/elasticsearch-paramedic\n",
      "- nothing to install\n",
      "\n",
      "bootstrap mloc = true\n",
      "ES_HEAP_SIZE = half ram\n",
      "keep other processes off ES box\n",
      "\n",
      "Open files:\n",
      "- crank up number of open files limit\n",
      "- /etc/security/limits.conf not allways work\n",
      "- use ulimit calls instead\n",
      "\n",
      "Use default stores:\n",
      "- performance increase not good enough\n",
      "- other stores not used enough to be battle tested\n",
      "- niofs is the way to go\n",
      "\n",
      "RAM & JVM tuning\n",
      "- default settings great\n",
      "- MAKE SURE YOU USE A MODERN JVM!!!!! at least >= 7.0\n",
      "- keep JVM heaps under 30GB, esp on large machines\n",
      "- filter cache - node status api, use default unless needed\n",
      "\n",
      "Shrinking indices\n",
      "- how big is my index?\n",
      "- how big is the hot part of my index?\n",
      "- computer speed times always I/O, so make efficient use of ram\n",
      "- vmstat -S m -a 2 ( warm up first with api )\n",
      "- turn off source field (\"_source\") - complete json document\n",
      "- if you just want doc_id then turn it off to save ram and disk, speeding things up (enabled: false)\n",
      "- alternatively just compress things (compressed: true)\n",
      "- \"_all\" - (enabled: false), or choose which fields to incorporate in _all\n",
      "\n",
      "Filter caching:\n",
      "\n",
      "Dealing with the future:\n",
      "- change mapping if you need with api, better deprecate old fields and add new fields\n",
      "\n",
      "How to re-index:\n",
      "- Use bulk api\n",
      "- turn off auto-refresh\n",
      "- set merge_factor: 1000 (won't defrag as excitedly)\n",
      "- remove replicas if you can\n",
      "- use multiple feeder processes\n",
      "- put everything back when done\n",
      "\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
